</emphasis>
occur in severely fragmented areas on high elevation (
<quantity box="[1300,1440,886,913]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="m" value="750.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="500.0">500–1000m</quantity>
). It has been collected within the “Reserva Particular do Patrimônio Natural Serra Bonita” and in the “Parque Nacional Serra das Lontras”. 
<taxonomicName box="[364,571,955,981]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[364,571,955,981]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an EOO of 
<quantity box="[761,868,956,984]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9769999999999999" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="km" value="1977.0">1,977 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity box="[1035,1123,956,984]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.78" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="km" value="378.0">378 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Endangered” (EN), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[495,645,990,1016]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="162" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,158,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1025,1051]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,500,1025,1051]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[294,500,1025,1051]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[665,733,1025,1051]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1208,1025,1051]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
), in humid and shady areas in the southeastern portion of the state. Collected with flowers in November and December, and fruits from August to April. 
<taxonomicName box="[323,528,1094,1120]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[323,528,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the leaf blade with dark green, bullate adaxial surface, sparsely glandulose-punctate and glandulose-villose (trichomes 
<quantity box="[775,916,1129,1156]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–3.5 mm</quantity>
long), and by the stem, abaxial leaf surface, hypanthium and sepals only glandulose-punctate. 
<taxonomicName box="[701,908,1163,1189]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[701,908,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bacci &amp; Michelangeli" authorityName="Bacci &amp; Michelangeli" box="[1059,1452,1163,1190]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis box="[1059,1194,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">B. vitoriana</emphasis>
Bacci &amp; Michelangeli
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[173,418,1198,1225]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis box="[242,290,1198,1224]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">et al</emphasis>
. 2018: 788
</bibRefCitation>
). Both have the stem, abaxial leaf surface, hypanthium and sepals glandulose-punctate, petals with an apiculate apex, anthers with an introrse pore and the connective prolonged below the thecae. 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1451,1233,1259]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[1247,1451,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Bertolonia bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[276,410,1268,1293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis box="[276,410,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">B. vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bullate leaf surface (
<emphasis box="[719,742,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">vs</emphasis>
. flat in 
<taxonomicName box="[828,961,1268,1293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitoriana">
<emphasis box="[828,961,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">B. vitoriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and petioles and adaxial surface of the leaf blade glandulose-villose (
<emphasis box="[424,447,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">vs</emphasis>
. petioles and adaxial surface of the leaf blade only glandulose-punctate). For more details, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B." box="[179,445,1337,1363]" pageId="9" pageNumber="162" pagination="273 - 279" refId="ref18825" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B. (2011) Two new species of Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Kew Bulletin 66: 273 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 011 - 9281 - 0" type="journal article" year="2011">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis box="[309,358,1337,1363]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="162">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[499,583,1337,1363]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." pageId="9" pageNumber="162">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
